│ THOUGHT: The miscompile comes from rewriting "sub y, (select c, x, (sub nsw 0, x))" into "add y, (select c, (sub nsw 0, x), x)". This likely happens when InstCombine converts "sub A,   │
│ B" into "add A, (neg B)" via the Negator, which then pushes negation through a select and swaps arms. To prevent exposing poison from "sub nsw 0, X", I will add a guard in              │
│ InstCombineAddSub.cpp right before attempting the "sub -> add + neg" rewrite: if the RHS is a select and either arm matches "sub nsw 0, V", skip converting sub to add. I'll search for  │
│ the Negator usage in AddSub combine and patch accordingly.                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ grep -RIn --exclude-dir=.git --exclude-dir=build 'Negator' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAddSub.cpp && \                                                                    │
│ python3 - << 'PY'                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ import re                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ p='llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAddSub.cpp'                                                                                                                                │
│ s=open(p,'r').read()                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ # Insert guard near any pattern that tries to rewrite sub as add with negation.                                                                                                          │
│ # We look for a common sequence invoking Negator or CreateNeg on Op1 then CreateAdd.                                                                                                     │
│ s = re.sub(r'(return\s+BinaryOperator::CreateNeg\(\s*Y\s*\);)', r'\1', s)                                                                                                                │
│ # Add a guard: if RHS is a select with a potentially-poisonous nsw negate arm, bail out before sub->add+neg.                                                                             │
│ guard_block = '''                                                                                                                                                                        │
│   // Guard: Do not rewrite "sub Op0, Op1" into "add Op0, (neg Op1)" if Op1 is a select                                                                                                   │
│   // whose arm is "sub nsw 0, V" because that can expose poison by swapping arms.                                                                                                        │
│   if (auto *Sel = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Op1)) {                                                                                                                                           │
│     using namespace llvm::PatternMatch;                                                                                                                                                  │
│     Value *TV = Sel->getTrueValue();                                                                                                                                                     │
│     Value *FV = Sel->getFalseValue();                                                                                                                                                    │
│     Value *NX;                                                                                                                                                                           │
│     bool TPoison = match(TV, m_Sub(m_Zero(), m_Value(NX))) &&                                                                                                                            │
│                    isa<BinaryOperator>(TV) &&                                                                                                                                            │
│                    cast<BinaryOperator>(TV)->hasNoSignedWrap();                                                                                                                          │
│     NX = nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                        │
│     bool FPoison = match(FV, m_Sub(m_Zero(), m_Value(NX))) &&                                                                                                                            │
│                    isa<BinaryOperator>(FV) &&                                                                                                                                            │
│                    cast<BinaryOperator>(FV)->hasNoSignedWrap();                                                                                                                          │
│     if (TPoison || FPoison)                                                                                                                                                              │
│       return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                    │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ '''                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ # Place the guard near the start of visitSub implementation, after obtaining Op0/Op1.                                                                                                    │
│ s = re.sub(r'(\bInstruction\s*\*InstCombine::visitSub\(BinaryOperator\s*&I\)\s*\{\s*[\s\S]*?Value\s*\*Op0\s*=\s*I\.getOperand\(0\);\s*Value\s*\*Op1\s*=\s*I\.getOperand\(1\);\s*)',      │
